        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 3 at 6:08PM PDT by NWS Medford OR</headline>
        <description>At 608 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
South Umpqua Falls Campground, or 29 miles northwest of Crater Lake,
moving north at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Boulder Flat Recreation Site, South Umpqua Falls Campground,
Horseshoe Bend Campground, Eagle Rock Campground, and Camp Comfort
Recreation Site.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
